Workflow 3 — QR Code Scanning & Attendance 

Description: 
This workflow explains how attendance is marked using QR code tickets. 

Steps: 
1. User arrives at the event venue. 
2. Organizer opens QR scanner in system. 
3. User presents QR code ticket. 
4. Organizer scans the QR code. 
5. System retrieves ticket data. 
6. System verifies ticket authenticity. 
7. If valid → entry is allowed. 
8. Attendance is marked automatically. 
9. Seat count is updated. 
10. If QR is scanned again → duplicate entry is blocked. 

Key Features Involved: 
● QR code validation 
● Attendance tracking 
● Real-time seat management 
● Fraud prevention
